# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to work for multiple versions of Python. With pyenv, this is usually
#   a version-specific directory.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having library installations that need consistency,
#   or if using different machines/operating systems, consider adding .venv to gitignore as well.
Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   This is especially recommended for binary packages to ensure reproducibility, and commonly ignored
#   for libraries.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
# pdm.lock

